# =============================================================================
# Railway — NanoMQ broker (Option A: repo root deploy)
# =============================================================================
# Do NOT commit real PEMs or keys. This file is a template only.
#
# Option A checklist (see broker/RAILWAY.txt):
#   • Root Directory: EMPTY (not broker/)
#   • Builder: Dockerfile — path broker/Dockerfile.nanomq (or use repo railway.toml)
#   • Optional env: RAILWAY_DOCKERFILE_PATH=broker/Dockerfile.nanomq
#
# How to fill:
#   1. Generate certs locally (see broker/README.txt).
#   2. In Railway Dashboard → your NanoMQ service → Variables → Raw Editor or per-var:
#      Paste each PEM as ONE variable value (multi-line is OK in the UI).
#   3. Redeploy the service.
#
# Required by docker-entrypoint.sh — all three must be set for Railway (no file mounts).
# =============================================================================

# --- Root CA (public) that signed broker.crt and your client certs ---
# Paste full file contents of: data/ca/root-ca.crt
NANOMQ_TLS_CA_CERT="-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
REPLACE_WITH_CONTENT_OF_root-ca.crt
-----END CERTIFICATE-----"

# --- Broker TLS certificate (server) ---
# Paste full file contents of: broker/certs/broker.crt
NANOMQ_TLS_CERT="-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
REPLACE_WITH_CONTENT_OF_broker.crt
-----END CERTIFICATE-----"

# --- Broker TLS private key (SECRET — treat like a password) ---
# Paste full file contents of: broker/certs/broker.key
# (Your file may say BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY — paste exactly as generated.)
NANOMQ_TLS_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----
REPLACE_WITH_CONTENT_OF_broker.key
-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"

# =============================================================================
# After deploy: Railway → Networking → TCP Proxy on port 8883
# Note the public hostname and external port, e.g.:
#   RAILWAY_TCP_HOST=xxxx.up.railway.app
#   RAILWAY_TCP_PORT=12345
# (Those two are NOT read by the broker container — write them down for your app.)
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: document here what your Node app (Render / local statsmqtt) should use
# (set these on Render or .env — NOT in Railway broker service)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# MQTT_BROKER=<RAILWAY_TCP_HOST from Networking tab>
# MQTT_PORT=<RAILWAY_TCP_PORT>
# MQTT_TLS_SERVERNAME=<CN inside broker.crt, e.g. nanomq-broker>  # if hostname ≠ cert CN
# MQTT_TLS_CA_PATH=./data/ca/root-ca.crt   # same CA as NANOMQ_TLS_CA_CERT
# MQTT_TLS_CLIENT_CERT_PATH=./broker/certs/client.crt
# MQTT_TLS_CLIENT_KEY_PATH=./broker/certs/client.key
# MQTT_USERNAME / MQTT_PASSWORD           # only if NanoMQ is configured for password auth
#
